    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1976-07-13T20:05:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1976-07-13T20:05:00-05:00" n="193"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d193">
                <head>193. Telegram 173878 From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss>
                    to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Kenya</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d193fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Policy Files, 1976. Secret; Niact
                        Immediate; Nodis. Drafted by Blake, cleared by <persName corresp="#p_HPC1"
                            >Habib</persName>, approved by <persName corresp="#p_ELS1"
                            >Eagleburger</persName>.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d193fn2">Secretary of State <persName
                            corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> instructed Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="#p_MAD2">Marshall</persName> to inform President <persName
                            corresp="#p_KJ1">Kenyatta</persName> that the United States had
                        stationed an aircraft carrier task force in the Indian Ocean.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1976-07-14T01:05:00+00:00">July 14, 1976, 0105Z</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>From the Secretary for Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MAD2">Marshall</persName>
                </p>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>Logistic flights and USS Ranger</item>
                </list>
                <list type="references">
                    <head>Reference:</head>
                    <item>Nairobi 7195</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. You may inform President <persName corresp="#p_KJ1">Kenyatta</persName> on my
                    behalf that in light of the situation now existing in East Africa we have
                    stationed an aircraft carrier task force in the Indian Ocean. If <persName
                        corresp="#p_KJ1">Kenyatta</persName> is not immediately available to you,
                    you may pass this information to whomever you believe would be most appropriate
                    in terms of conveying it soonest to <persName corresp="#p_KJ1"
                        >Kenyatta</persName>, but you should make sure it is understood as a message
                    from me to the President.</p>
                <p>2. You are authorized to make whatever arrangements are necessary for logistic
                    flights between Nairobi, Mombassa and the Ranger after you have passed the above
                    message.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
